description: Data was extracted from MDAnderson Functional Proteomics RPPA Core Facility on July 2016. Protein expression data was generated using all the data produced by MDAnderson Functional Proteomics RPPA Core Facility.

fields.description: TCGA barcode identifier for the study participant, eg TCGA-02-0001
fields.name: ParticipantBarcode

fields.description: TCGA sample barcode, eg TCGA-12-1089-01A. One sample may have multiple sets of CN segmentations corresponding to multiple aliquots; use GROUP BY appropriately in queries
fields.name: SampleBarcode

fields.description: Letter code of the sample type using the TCGA standards, eg TPN, EBV. Full list available at https://gdc.cancer.gov/resources-TCGA-users/TCGA-code-tables/sample-type-codes
fields.name: SampleTypeLetterCode

fields.description: TCGA study abbreviation, eg LAML. Full list available at https://gdc.cancer.gov/resources-TCGA-users/TCGA-code-tables/TCGA-study-abbreviations
fields.name: Study

fields.description: The Gene name is the gene symbol.Examples:SHC1, JUN, MAPK8, BAD, GYS1
fields.name: Gene_Name

fields.description: Protein_Expression.Expression level of protein as measured by reverse-phase protein arrays (RPPAs).Examples: 0.204238725,-0.01826295
fields.name: Protein_Expression

fields.description: Protein symbol with phosphorylation status, eg ACC_pS79. Other examples: p38_pT180_Y182 , 4E-BP1_pS65
fields.name: Protein_Name

fields.description: Protein_Basename. Examples: ATM, Axl, Bid, TAZ, p53, etc.
fields.name: Protein_Basename

fields.description: Phosphorylated residue/s of protein.Examples: pS536, pT37_T46, pS1943. If the antibody targets a phosphorylated protein, this field will contain that information, eg pS473--otherwise this field will be null
fields.name: Phospho

fields.description: There are three possible values: R, M, and G. That is, the animal of origin for the antibody can be M (Mouse), R (Rabbit), G (Goat)
fields.name: antibodySource

fields.description: Validation status of antibody by correlation of RPPA data with Western blot: V, E, C. For more information: https://bioinformatics.mdanderson.org/public-software/mclp/
fields.name: validationStatus
